text:
Always enjoyed having my Low Fat Vanilla Latte at Starbucks.

OTH is a good location with friendly staff.

It can get a bit crowded during weekends and school breaks when students are studying and enjoying food and drinks.

I like the setting and feel tranquil as most are respectful of the students studying (I guessing) and do not speak too loudly.

No doubt THE beat Starbucks in the East

Polite staff and quick service. Even recently when my coffee was poorly done they acknowledged and replaced my drink.

My go to outlet

Very cosy starbucks outlet even though it can get really crowded. Some seats were too close to each other though, so really depends where u get.

Standard is there so nothing much to comment!
Best part is that this is a 24h joint. Service was really good and friendly when I visited.

Tried the expensive $8.90 chocolate lava cake. The chcolate flavour is not strong enough and it is overly sweet. The cake is very dense and not moist. Not worth $8.90. Other bakeries sell better cakes.
